post_text:
Some info from Coach Mestas to go with the picture just posted:

A little tradition that was started with Jesus "Chuy" Barraza ten years ago. Chuy is a petroleum engineer in Houston now working with Chevron. That was my first year.

We went 25-8 and made it to the Final 4 that year. 2006 we went 26-6 and went to Final 4. 2007 we went 20-8. 2008 we went 26-3 and went to the Final 4. 2009 we were 23-4. 2010 we went 25-5 and went to the Final 4. 2011 went 31-0 and won it all. 2012 we went 18-12 and made it to the Elite 8. 2013 we went 25-5 and were state runner-ups. 2014 we went 26-4 and won it all.

Overall record of 245-55. 10 years strong!!üèÄüëçüëä

Thank you so much players for giving it your all for Hagerman Basketball.

post_text:
We're going to the 'ship!!!!

Bobcats came up with the big win tonight to advance to the state championship game. Final score was Hagerman 60, Springer 45. JB led all scorers with 17 points, Bryan added 14 including 2 clutch 3 pointers, Jessie added 12, Jandro 11, and Jorge chipped in 6.

The boys played an excellent game and are one win away being state champions! Game time is 6 pm on Saturday at THE PIT.

Let's go Bobcats! Take state!!!

post_text:
Hagerman High School boys basketball is pleased to announce that we are kicking off our Spirit Cup Fundraiser. Spirit Cups are a set of 4 cups designed with exclusive 3-D animation, durable dishwasher-safe plastic, 18 oz. capacity, are made in the USA and BPA free.

Each set of 4 cups sells for $15.00. Our sales begin tomorrow and will end Oct. 11th. Cash or checks are acceptable forms of payment. Checks should be made out to Hagerman Basketball. Payment for cups need to be in by Oct. 11th.

Cups include NFL, MLB, College, NFL Pink, and the U.S. Military. Basketball players will have order forms and will be visiting you soon. Money will be used to help pay for shoes and team shirts.

Thanks for the support
